Author::::nearmuse
DateTime::::2016-02-25T23:08:54Z
I have an ipad (4) and a (cheap moto e) android phone. The ipad is the better hardware, clearly and is a pleasure to use. However comparing Android lollipop with ios 9.2, I feel Android is pulling ahead. The article mentions notifications, quick settings and task switching, all of which I agree with. I never use IOS notifications, I just notice the bubbles and click on the app. I use Android notifications all the time (often without opening the app). Task switching is easier in Android, and the links between apps is better (and you can choose which app opens).There are also simple things about Android which just work better - when I get to work my phone switches itself to silent (built-in moto active app) and switches back when I leave. I can't seem to do that on an iphone. The big plus about the ipad is the quality of the hardware (again) and the long-term support. My Android phone may get 6.0 if it's lucky (eventually) - my ipad is gone all the way from ios 6 to ios 9, and will probably get 10 as well.



